Cigarettes. Cigarettes.

83
00:11:02,034 --> 00:11:03,166
Which one?

84
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:05,165
Dunhill.

85
00:11:06,857 --> 00:11:08,076
Which Dunhill?

86
00:11:09,056 --> 00:11:10,147
1mg.

87
00:11:14,619 --> 00:11:16,144
It's 2,500 won.

88
00:11:16,227 --> 00:11:17,786
No, not that one.

89
00:11:18,672 --> 00:11:20,878
This is 1mg.

90
00:11:20,961 --> 00:11:25,386
You know, the other one. The thin one.

91
00:11:27,396 --> 00:11:28,768
Do you mean Fine Cut 1mg?

92
00:11:29,398 --> 00:11:32,107
No, not that one.

93
00:11:32,841 --> 00:11:34,692
Then what? What do you want?

94
00:11:34,775 --> 00:11:36,629
The one that costs 2,000 won.

95
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:45,002
- Pocket 1mg?
- Yes, that one.

96
00:11:45,085 --> 00:11:46,314
Give me one of those.

97
00:11:55,382 --> 00:11:56,625
It's 2,000 won.

98
00:11:58,449 --> 00:12:02,788
Geez. Does it have to be this hard...

99
00:12:04,919 --> 00:12:06,170
to buy cigarettes?

100
00:12:08,832 --> 00:12:10,547
Is it that hard?

101
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:11,993
Goodbye.

102
00:12:24,915 --> 00:12:28,055
OFFICE ASSISTANT/CLERICAL
COLLEGE DEGREE

103
00:12:28,138 --> 00:12:29,635
MARAIS COLLECTION
DEGREE NOT REQUIRED

104
00:12:31,802 --> 00:12:33,898
MARAIS COLLECTION
DEGREE NOT REQUIRED

105
00:12:33,981 --> 00:12:36,488
FEMALES BETWEEN 20 AND 35
DEGREE NOT REQUIRED

106
00:14:15,726 --> 00:14:16,749
Hey.

107
00:14:50,997 --> 00:14:52,592
Are you still waiting?

108
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:13,048
Right!

109
00:15:13,806 --> 00:15:15,177
You're waiting for me, right?

110
00:15:15,694 --> 00:15:17,089
I'm sorry.

111
00:15:19,535 --> 00:15:20,561
Dad!

112
00:15:21,502 --> 00:15:23,564
Just tell my dad you'll work hard,

113
00:15:23,647 --> 00:15:24,960
and he'll hire you.

114
00:15:27,983 --> 00:15:29,334
Hey. Where's Dad?

115
00:15:29,963 --> 00:15:32,432
He went to a church event
with Big Director.

116
00:15:32,515 --> 00:15:33,488
I see.

117
00:15:33,571 --> 00:15:35,705
They said they'll be home late.

118
00:15:35,788 --> 00:15:37,720
You can do the interview
and make the decision.

119
00:15:37,803 --> 00:15:39,313
- I'm going out.
- Me?

120
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:41,784
Why not? I'll give Dad a heads-up.

121
00:15:44,469 --> 00:15:46,107
Yes? Hello?

122
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:47,216
Yes.

123
00:15:48,902 --> 00:15:51,393
I thought she was taking her time
with the interview.

124
00:15:51,476 --> 00:15:52,626
It's all right.

125
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:58,529
It's family-run here,
so it's a bit different.

126
00:15:58,612 --> 00:16:00,326
Tell me right away
if it's not for you.

127
00:16:00,795 --> 00:16:03,308
Some people don't show up
after just a day or two.

128
00:16:03,391 --> 00:16:05,026
That can take a toll on us too.

129
00:16:05,879 --> 00:16:06,912
Okay.

130
00:16:11,515 --> 00:16:13,852
The owner was born and raised here.

131
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:17,160
I heard he majored in the arts,

132
00:16:17,243 --> 00:16:19,616
but none of us know exactly what.

133
00:16:21,291 --> 00:16:23,335
They all call him Designer Lee.

134
00:16:26,314 --> 00:16:27,911
RESUME

135
00:16:28,557 --> 00:16:29,865
You only graduated high school.

136
00:16:30,692 --> 00:16:31,701
Yes.

137
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:36,896
I'm only allowing it
because my daughter wants to hire you.

138
00:16:39,443 --> 00:16:40,975
Ms. Kim must have told you already,

139
00:16:41,764 --> 00:16:45,688
but tardiness and no shows
aren't tolerated.

140
00:16:47,126 --> 00:16:47,958
I understand.

141
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:49,736
Make sure nothing makes
Hyun-joo uncomfortable.

142
00:16:49,819 --> 00:16:52,156
Stick by her side and focus on that.

143
00:16:52,239 --> 00:16:55,864
The most important thing to me
is keeping promises.

144
00:16:58,453 --> 00:16:59,592
Can you do it?

145
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:04,775
All the furniture here

146
00:17:04,858 --> 00:17:07,125
are by famous designers
and were imported from abroad.

147
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:09,005
They're expensive.

148
00:17:09,088 --> 00:17:12,855
That little chair costs 15 million won.

149
00:17:12,938 --> 00:17:14,993
Patoulji Melissa Manu.

150
00:17:17,166 --> 00:17:18,217
I got it right.

151
00:17:19,526 --> 00:17:20,737
I memorized them all.

152
00:17:29,177 --> 00:17:34,029
Herman Miller.
Eames Lounge Chair and Ottoman in white.

153
00:17:35,585 --> 00:17:39,058
The Olive Garden is managed
by Mr. Lee's wife.

154
00:17:39,937 --> 00:17:42,690
We call her Big Director.

155
00:17:43,432 --> 00:17:45,668
She often holds church gatherings here.

156
00:17:45,751 --> 00:17:47,932
In addition to nurturing our bodies,

157
00:17:48,015 --> 00:17:52,077
please allow our spirits to be nurtured

158
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,259
as well.

159
00:17:55,473 --> 00:17:57,681
Thank you, Father.

160
00:17:57,764 --> 00:18:00,215
We'll enjoy the food.

161
00:18:01,146 --> 00:18:02,454
- Amen.
- Amen.

162
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:08,407
What is this?

163
00:18:10,315 --> 00:18:13,407
Gosh, what is this?

164
00:18:14,421 --> 00:18:17,762
What is this, Deaconess?

165
00:18:17,845 --> 00:18:20,352
It's thanks to you
that my daughter's marriage is in talks.

166
00:18:20,435 --> 00:18:23,649
This is the least I can do.

167
00:18:23,732 --> 00:18:25,928
Your daughter is already perfect
in every way.

168
00:18:26,011 --> 00:18:27,960
She doesn't need us to get married.

169
00:18:29,253 --> 00:18:33,443
It was my wish to get a doctor son-in-law.

170
00:18:33,526 --> 00:18:35,212
My wish is going to come true.

171
00:18:35,295 --> 00:18:38,579
I'm thankful for all the support from you.

172
00:18:38,662 --> 00:18:41,106
If you wanted a doctor in the family,

173
00:18:41,189 --> 00:18:43,472
why didn't you raise her to be a doctor?

174
00:18:43,555 --> 00:18:47,481
Gosh, how could I make my child
have such an exhausting job?

175
00:18:47,564 --> 00:18:50,343
Yes. They say you should never
raise your child as a doctor or a lawyer.

176
00:18:50,426 --> 00:18:51,463
You can just hire them.

177
00:18:51,546 --> 00:18:53,207
You're right.

178
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:54,941
That's true.

179
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:57,748
- We'll enjoy this.
- Thank you.

180
00:18:58,589 --> 00:19:02,055
You met Little Director earlier.
She's Mr. Lee's daughter.

181
00:19:02,918 --> 00:19:04,421
I bought this.

182
00:19:05,109 --> 00:19:06,084
Welcome back.

183
00:19:06,167 --> 00:19:08,035
She's the only child, so she's fussy.

184
00:19:09,424 --> 00:19:11,501
She moved back from the US last year,

185
00:19:11,584 --> 00:19:13,394
and runs a prop shop.

186
00:19:15,264 --> 00:19:16,290
Isn't it pretty?

187
00:19:18,432 --> 00:19:21,433
I went to the store,
and this was the last one left.

188
00:19:22,384 --> 00:19:23,970
I wanted the orange one too.

189
00:19:32,256 --> 00:19:33,395
You can have this.

190
00:19:38,035 --> 00:19:39,303
I'm okay.

191
00:19:41,269 --> 00:19:44,879
What's the matter?
Is it because it's used?

192
00:19:45,813 --> 00:19:48,049
You should dress up a little.

193
00:19:49,004 --> 00:19:50,470
This is expensive stuff.

194
00:19:58,090 --> 00:19:59,397
Thank you.

195
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:07,554
I went to the car wash
to wash my car this morning,

196
00:20:08,606 --> 00:20:10,576
but I walked there since it was close.

197
00:20:13,494 --> 00:20:16,460
Little Director is often away,

198
00:20:17,275 --> 00:20:20,703
so the person in charge of this place
will only get a day off in a month.

199
00:20:23,129 --> 00:20:26,616
Some of the items
are imported from abroad,

200
00:20:26,699 --> 00:20:29,534
but most of them are from the market.

201
00:20:31,515 --> 00:20:33,271
Is this from Namdaemun Market too?

202
00:20:33,354 --> 00:20:34,358
Yes.

203
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:37,959
How much is that one you're holding?

204
00:20:42,675 --> 00:20:44,127
This is 66,000 won.

205
00:20:44,723 --> 00:20:45,812
That?

206
00:20:47,844 --> 00:20:49,503
The finish is lousy.

207
00:20:51,827 --> 00:20:55,149
Place it beside the ivory mirror.

208
00:20:56,185 --> 00:20:57,853
Mark it as 260,000 won.

209
00:20:57,936 --> 00:20:58,907
Okay.

210
00:20:59,888 --> 00:21:04,105
To be honest,
it's more of an administrative position

211
00:21:04,188 --> 00:21:05,736
than an office job.

212
00:21:09,157 --> 00:21:11,379
You'll be paid 1 million won for 3 months.

213
00:21:11,462 --> 00:21:13,662
After that,
it'll be 1.3 million won a month.

214
00:21:15,183 --> 00:21:16,490
Hello?

215
00:21:23,521 --> 00:21:27,349
You only worked part-time for five years.

216
00:21:28,803 --> 00:21:30,612
This will still be better
than a part-time job.

217
00:21:31,369 --> 00:21:34,581
At least you get an insurance.

218
00:21:48,156 --> 00:21:49,156
Mom.

219
00:21:50,241 --> 00:21:51,979
We have health insurance now,

220
00:21:52,062 --> 00:21:55,247
so make sure
to go to the doctor regularly. Okay?

221
00:21:56,839 --> 00:21:58,330
Tap twice if you understood.

222
00:22:13,012 --> 00:22:15,302
What? Is that a fire?

223
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:17,153
Where?

224
00:22:18,046 --> 00:22:18,951
There.

225
00:22:19,648 --> 00:22:20,846
Gosh, how did that happen?

226
00:22:22,329 --> 00:22:24,612
There's a fire.

227
00:22:24,695 --> 00:22:25,662
My goodness.

228
00:22:28,379 --> 00:22:30,616
We just received breaking news

229
00:22:30,699 --> 00:22:33,025
that Korea's number one national treasure,
Namdaemun, is on fire.

230
00:22:33,108 --> 00:22:34,940
Reporter Kim Jung-hoon,
please share the story.

231
00:22:35,369 --> 00:22:37,159
For the first 30 minutes
after the fire was spotted,

232
00:22:37,242 --> 00:22:39,142
smoke rose above the rooftop.

233
00:22:39,225 --> 00:22:42,856
The fire remained out of control
even after an hour.

234
00:22:42,939 --> 00:22:45,230
At 9:59 p.m., the fire authorities

235
00:22:45,313 --> 00:22:47,527
declared level two in fire emergency,

