is because you're friends with his son.

472
00:47:46,851 --> 00:47:49,042
What? No way!

473
00:47:49,125 --> 00:47:51,192
- I'm right.
- No, you're wrong.

474
00:47:51,275 --> 00:47:52,270
Excuse me.

475
00:47:53,244 --> 00:47:54,536
What is it?

476
00:47:55,172 --> 00:47:57,513
Your passport expires in a month.

477
00:47:59,899 --> 00:48:01,174
Get it reissued.

478
00:48:07,499 --> 00:48:09,446
It's something you should know
to do automatically.

479
00:48:12,826 --> 00:48:14,000
Okay.

480
00:48:14,083 --> 00:48:15,205
Get it expedited.

481
00:48:17,937 --> 00:48:20,586
Do I have to tell you everything?

482
00:48:21,816 --> 00:48:22,844
No.

483
00:48:31,753 --> 00:48:33,491
She can really get on my nerves.

484
00:48:38,121 --> 00:48:39,341
You can go back to work.

485
00:48:49,969 --> 00:48:51,180
That looks delicious.

486
00:48:55,289 --> 00:48:57,222
You're not going anywhere.

487
00:48:57,305 --> 00:48:58,844
Yu-mi is here.

488
00:49:00,401 --> 00:49:03,278
It's the end of the year.
We should have a nice time too.

489
00:49:03,361 --> 00:49:05,747
She's right. The mafia family is out.

490
00:49:06,688 --> 00:49:08,494
Turn off the carol.

491
00:49:08,577 --> 00:49:11,827
It makes me want to throw up every season.

492
00:49:13,953 --> 00:49:15,758
I heard Big Director talk earlier,

493
00:49:15,841 --> 00:49:17,716
and Little Director is getting married
next spring.

494
00:49:19,007 --> 00:49:21,036
It's taking so long to plan this marriage.

495
00:49:21,655 --> 00:49:23,029
Has it been two years now?

496
00:49:23,112 --> 00:49:27,100
They're rich,
but the family isn't that powerful.

497
00:49:27,183 --> 00:49:29,278
- With that hospital owner's son?
- Yes.

498
00:49:29,956 --> 00:49:33,647
What is that about? I saw Little Director
get picked up by another guy earlier.

499
00:49:34,219 --> 00:49:38,352
Everyone in this family
has dual citizenship.

500
00:49:38,435 --> 00:49:39,597
It's the American way.

501
00:49:46,826 --> 00:49:48,941
Yu-mi, were you upset earlier?

502
00:49:51,930 --> 00:49:54,545
Little Director made it worse.

503
00:49:54,628 --> 00:49:57,928
One day they tell you you're inflexible,

504
00:49:58,011 --> 00:49:59,803
then on another,
they're strict about principles.

505
00:49:59,886 --> 00:50:01,525
Why didn't you tell me?

506
00:50:02,964 --> 00:50:06,683
You have to start flattering him
a few days before asking for a day off.

507
00:50:06,766 --> 00:50:09,709
It's really hard for us and Yu-mi.

508
00:50:09,792 --> 00:50:11,692
We take turns taking a day off a month.

509
00:50:11,775 --> 00:50:13,420
He's right.

510
00:50:13,503 --> 00:50:16,081
I'm always so tired
the day after we receive a delivery.

511
00:50:27,508 --> 00:50:29,433
He called us stupid and lazy.

512
00:50:32,334 --> 00:50:34,978
I thought about it all day long
after hearing that from him.

513
00:50:35,061 --> 00:50:38,153
It offended me too.

514
00:50:38,932 --> 00:50:41,391
Mr. Lee is especially harsh on Yu-mi.

515
00:50:41,474 --> 00:50:44,710
He looked down on her last time
for not having a degree.

516
00:50:45,602 --> 00:50:47,535
If they're so educated,

517
00:50:47,618 --> 00:50:49,944
why sell stuff from the market?

518
00:50:50,027 --> 00:50:51,206
Watch what you say.

519
00:50:52,396 --> 00:50:54,648
We know what Mr. Lee is like.

520
00:50:54,731 --> 00:50:56,689
This is how it works in the real world.

521
00:50:56,772 --> 00:50:57,952
It's normal.

522
00:51:01,260 --> 00:51:02,845
Ms. Kim.

523
00:51:04,877 --> 00:51:07,463
Does it taste good to drink stolen wine?

524
00:51:11,654 --> 00:51:13,241
Do you hear yourself?

525
00:51:13,324 --> 00:51:16,497
Don't be like that, Yu-mi.

526
00:51:16,580 --> 00:51:17,725
As for me,

527
00:51:21,130 --> 00:51:23,565
I don't have the courage
to live like this forever.

528
00:51:25,275 --> 00:51:26,494
Geez.

529
00:51:27,940 --> 00:51:29,517
So what will you do?

530
00:51:40,713 --> 00:51:46,029
I want people to fear me.

531
00:53:23,715 --> 00:53:25,049
I'll take one of these.

532
00:53:34,307 --> 00:53:36,502
Wait! Just a minute!

533
00:53:37,836 --> 00:53:38,807
Just a minute.

534
00:53:39,966 --> 00:53:40,999
Thank you.

535
00:53:42,191 --> 00:53:45,760
SEOUL TO HONGCHEON

536
00:53:48,460 --> 00:53:50,623
Don't go. Just five more minutes.

537
00:53:56,411 --> 00:53:59,218
Wait here.
I'll make you something delicious.

538
00:53:59,356 --> 00:54:01,510
Something delicious? Okay

