00:54:29,173 --> 00:54:30,169
DELETED

541
00:54:30,239 --> 00:54:31,994
MARAIS DIRECTOR

542
00:54:33,035 --> 00:54:33,900
DELETED

543
00:54:45,489 --> 00:54:48,401
JI-WON

544
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:01,705
Hello?

545
00:55:02,223 --> 00:55:03,375
Hello.

546
00:55:04,141 --> 00:55:05,192
Yes?

547
00:55:06,814 --> 00:55:11,023
Is this Ji-won's number?

548
00:55:11,805 --> 00:55:13,360
Yes, it is. Who is this?

549
00:55:15,373 --> 00:55:16,807
It's me, Yu-mi.

550
00:55:17,725 --> 00:55:18,811
Yu-mi?

551
00:55:18,894 --> 00:55:20,351
Yes, Yu-mi.

552
00:55:25,236 --> 00:55:27,519
So, were you in America all this time?

553
00:55:28,581 --> 00:55:30,686
Yes. I went to school there.

554
00:55:36,012 --> 00:55:38,635
Why do you feel so much calmer?

555
00:55:38,718 --> 00:55:41,234
I don't think I would've recognized you
on the streets.

556
00:55:42,007 --> 00:55:44,236
People aren't as conscious
about other people there.

557
00:55:45,191 --> 00:55:47,207
So? Are you back for good?

558
00:55:47,290 --> 00:55:49,453
Yes, I'm back for good.

559
00:55:52,114 --> 00:55:53,663
I came back,

560
00:55:53,746 --> 00:55:56,732
but I'm not sure where to start.

561
00:56:04,802 --> 00:56:08,188
I see. But I don't know either.

562
00:56:09,081 --> 00:56:11,020
I didn't get into
any of the places I wanted.

563
00:56:11,103 --> 00:56:13,138
The place I'm at now is tiny.

564
00:56:15,528 --> 00:56:18,918
But at least you became a reporter
like you wanted.

565
00:56:20,064 --> 00:56:21,806
It's just my luck.

566
00:56:21,889 --> 00:56:23,787
It takes forever
whenever I try to do something.

567
00:56:23,870 --> 00:56:25,415
It took me two years
to get admitted to our university.

568
00:56:27,047 --> 00:56:28,441
You're just a late bloomer.

569
00:56:30,382 --> 00:56:34,153
Actually, I hated this company at first.

570
00:56:34,236 --> 00:56:39,319
Oh, well. How I got here isn't important.

571
00:56:39,402 --> 00:56:42,556
The issue is how I'll handle it
in the future.

572
00:56:44,291 --> 00:56:46,248
So, what kind of work do you want to do?

573
00:56:46,331 --> 00:56:48,582
I have connections.
I work for the alumni association.

574
00:56:49,219 --> 00:56:51,910
No, no. I didn't call you
to ask you for a favor.

575
00:56:52,786 --> 00:56:54,743
Do you want to teach kids part-time?

576
00:56:54,826 --> 00:56:56,967
People would welcome
someone like you with open arms.

577
00:57:00,993 --> 00:57:02,464
What kind of job is it?

578
00:57:02,547 --> 00:57:05,295
I know someone who runs an art academy.

579
00:57:05,378 --> 00:57:07,474
Her academy is big and famous.

580
00:57:08,766 --> 00:57:10,438
Your degree is in the arts, right?

581
00:57:14,320 --> 00:57:17,305
LEE YU-MI, MARCH 29, 1981

582
00:57:21,855 --> 00:57:23,898
ACADEMIC BACKGROUND

583
00:57:29,007 --> 00:57:32,171
How I got here isn't important.

584
00:57:32,254 --> 00:57:35,337
The issue is how I'll handle it
in the future.

